        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer28894334" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6230432497014874473">I have fond memories of this book. I have a feeling Peter could have certainly benefited (christian or no) from the serenity prayer. Perhaps he&apos;ll eventually pick it up at a meeting of Fudgaholics Anonymous. <br/><br/>Blume&apos;s humor and ability to speak to deeply-rooted juvenile issues (such as being utterly ignored) keep her firmly planted at the pinnacle of authors writing for young readers. When the mood strikes me and if there&apos;s a copy handy I&apos;ll read just the last page of this book. I walk away unders</span>
  <span id="freeText6230432497014874473" style="display:none">I have fond memories of this book. I have a feeling Peter could have certainly benefited (christian or no) from the serenity prayer. Perhaps he'll eventually pick it up at a meeting of Fudgaholics Anonymous. <br /><br />Blume's humor and ability to speak to deeply-rooted juvenile issues (such as being utterly ignored) keep her firmly planted at the pinnacle of authors writing for young readers. When the mood strikes me and if there's a copy handy I'll read just the last page of this book. I walk away understanding that loss and gain are intertwined and that no matter how messed up life gets, what matters is how one handles life's adversities.</span>
